---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "86 Chaos | Kitchen Management OS for Independent Restaurants";
const description = "86 Chaos helps independent restaurants save manager time, improve ordering decisions, protect food cost, and keep prep, 86s, schedules, inventory, and daily operations visible.";
const ogTitle = "86 Chaos | Kitchen Management OS for Independent Restaurants";
const ogDescription = "Save manager time, improve ordering decisions, protect food cost, and keep daily kitchen operations visible with 86 Chaos.";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  page="home"
  canonicalPath="/"
  ogTitle={ogTitle}
  ogDescription={ogDescription}
>
<main id="main">

    <section class="hero section-tight">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Limited Founder Beta • independent restaurants</p>
          <h1>Run the kitchen without running yourself <span>ragged.</span></h1>
          <p class="hero-lede">86 Chaos helps independent restaurants save manager time, reduce shift confusion, improve ordering decisions, protect food cost, and keep daily operations visible without a giant enterprise system.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button" href="beta.html">Apply Free</a>
            <a class="button ghost" href="product-tour.html">Product Tour</a>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-proof">
            <span><b>90 days</b> free</span>
            <span><b>No card</b> required</span>
            <span><b>No purchase</b> required</span>
            <span><b>Unlimited users</b> included</span>
            <span><b>Free setup</b> during beta</span>
            <span><b>50% off</b> first location</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-product reveal delay-1" aria-label="86 Chaos product screenshots">
          <div class="screen-stack">
            <img class="screen primary-shot" src="assets/prep.webp" alt="86 Chaos live prep screen" />
            <img class="screen floating-shot one" src="assets/inventory.webp" alt="86 Chaos invoice screen" />
            <img class="screen floating-shot two" src="assets/schedule.webp" alt="86 Chaos schedule screen" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cred-strip">
      <div class="container cred-grid">
        <img src="assets/map-logo.webp" alt="86 Chaos Wisconsin map brand graphic" />
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Built on the line. Not in a boardroom.</p>
          <h2>Practical tools for the things managers chase every day.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="cred-items">
          <span>Prep, 86s, schedules, and reminders</span>
          <span>Ordering, invoices, waste, and par visibility</span>
          <span>Manager Brief attention without the scavenger hunt</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section compact-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head center reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Less chaos. More control.</p>
          <h2>Replace the pile of notes, texts, spreadsheets, and memory.</h2>
          <p>86 Chaos gives managers one practical place to see what needs attention, what is running low, what prep is unfinished, what the schedule is doing, and what the kitchen should review next.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="compact-feature-list two-col reveal">
          <div><strong>Save manager time</strong><span>Manager Brief, 86Voice, reminders, prep status, and daily attention items reduce the hunt for answers.</span></div>
          <div><strong>Protect food cost</strong><span>Invoice price warnings, waste/par insights, prep prediction, and smarter order drafts make costly patterns easier to catch.</span></div>
          <div><strong>Keep the shift visible</strong><span>Prep, tasks, 86 alerts, schedules, availability, maintenance, and team communication stay in one operating picture.</span></div>
          <div><strong>Make adoption easier</strong><span>Start with one useful workflow and use 86Voice when tapping through another screen would slow the shift down.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="panel reveal" style="padding:16px">
          <p class="eyebrow">Easy first step</p>
          <h2>Start with the problem that wastes the most time.</h2>
          <p>Pick prep, 86 alerts, reminders, schedules, ordering, or another daily headache. Founder Beta includes free setup help, so the restaurant does not have to build the entire operation before the app becomes useful.</p>
          <div class="audit-list">
            <span>Choose one workflow that already causes friction.</span>
            <span>Set up the minimum needed to test it on a real shift.</span>
            <span>Add more tools only after the team is comfortable.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="phone-frame reveal delay-1"><img src="assets/recipes.webp" alt="86 Chaos recipe book screen" /></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    
    
    
    <section class="section feature-band">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Everything in one place</p>
          <h2>One operating layer for daily restaurant work.</h2>
          <p>86 Chaos brings prep, 86 alerts, schedules, inventory, invoices, recipes, maintenance, reminders, and manager follow-up into one organized workspace. Smart Kitchen and Owner Pro add the intelligence layer for ordering support, menu impact, cost visibility, reporting, and owner/admin controls.</p>
          <a class="button" href="features.html">View Full Feature Map</a>
        </div>
        <div class="panel mini-dashboard reveal delay-1">
          <h3>Feature coverage</h3>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Daily ops</span><strong>Today, prep, messages, reminders</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Kitchen tools</span><strong>86Voice, recipes, menu impact</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Cost control</span><strong>Invoices, inventory, burn logs</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>People</span><strong>Schedules, labor, HR</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row good"><span>Owner visibility</span><strong>Financials, reports, audit logs</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    
    <section class="section ai-first-strip">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head center reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Why the AI matters</p>
          <h2>AI is built into the workflows that affect time, food cost, and manager decisions.</h2>
          <p>86 Chaos uses AI to reduce manager chasing, improve ordering decisions, catch price and waste problems, connect ingredients to menu impact, and surface what needs attention before it becomes another fire to put out.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-4">
          <div class="note-box reveal"><strong>Order smarter</strong><span>AI-assisted ordering turns stock, par, invoices, waste, events, prep, and vendors into reviewable order drafts.</span></div>
          <div class="note-box reveal delay-1"><strong>Catch cost leaks</strong><span>Price jumps, duplicate invoices, waste patterns, par issues, and recipe/menu cost signals become easier to see.</span></div>
          <div class="note-box reveal delay-2"><strong>Move faster</strong><span>86Voice lets managers create prep, tasks, reminders, 86s, messages, waste logs, events, and status checks without digging.</span></div>
          <div class="note-box reveal delay-3"><strong>Keep humans in control</strong><span>AI suggests, explains, drafts, alerts, analyzes, and reports. Managers approve business-changing actions.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section roi-section">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">How it earns its spot</p>
          <h2>Practical value shows up in the little daily misses.</h2>
          <p>Even small daily improvements can make the app worth it: fewer missed prep items, fewer scattered notes, clearer handoffs, better ordering review, and less manager chasing.</p>
          <div class="audit-list">
            <span>Prep, 86 alerts, reminders, and handoff notes stay in one place.</span>
            <span>Ordering review gets more context from inventory, invoices, waste, par levels, and menu impact.</span>
            <span>Managers can spot repeat problems without relying on memory, texts, or paper piles.</span>
          </div>
          <a class="button" href="pricing.html">See pricing plans</a>
        </div>
        <div class="roi-card panel reveal delay-1">
          <p class="eyebrow">Beta-honest value</p>
          <h3>Less chasing. Better handoffs. Clearer review.</h3>
          <p>86 Chaos is meant to prove itself through practical restaurant workflows first, then grow into the deeper intelligence tools as beta feedback comes in.</p>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Best starting point</span><strong>One real workflow</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row good"><span>Goal</span><strong>Cleaner daily control</strong></div>
          <small>No calculator magic. The app should earn trust by making the shift easier to run.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    
    
    <section class="section app-alignment-section beta-reality-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head center reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Current beta reality</p>
          <h2>Already useful in real shifts, with newer tools being tested carefully.</h2>
          <p>Schedule and time clock workflows have already been used in a real restaurant environment, while newer tools like AI ordering, Back Office, QuickBooks review, and advanced reporting are being tested through controlled Founder Beta.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-2 beta-reality-grid">
          <div class="note-box reveal"><strong>Already tested in real workflows</strong><span>Schedule Builder, time clock workflows, prep/task coordination, handoffs, and daily kitchen visibility.</span></div>
          <div class="note-box reveal delay-1"><strong>Controlled Founder Beta testing</strong><span>AI ordering, Smart Kitchen Intelligence, Back Office, QuickBooks review, owner dashboards, and advanced reporting.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
<section class="section ai-tools-section">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">AI Tools</p>
          <h2>AI tools that help managers catch problems sooner.</h2>
          <p>86 Chaos connects AI to the work managers already do: ordering, invoices, waste, par levels, prep, Menu Intelligence, and Manager Brief. It is built to surface useful signals and prepare reviewable work, not make unchecked decisions.</p>
          <div class="audit-list">
            <span>Voice commands for prep, tasks, reminders, 86s, events, maintenance, waste, and status questions.</span>
            <span>Ordering intelligence for vendor drafts, event supply planning, prep prediction, and invoice price warnings.</span>
            <span>Forecasting and operational analysis for waste patterns, par recommendations, menu costing, labor pressure, and urgent attention items.</span>
          </div>
          <a class="button" href="ai-tools.html">See AI Tools</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-suite-card panel reveal delay-1">
          <p class="eyebrow">AI in 86 Chaos</p>
          <h3>Suggest. Explain. Draft. Alert. Analyze. Report.</h3>
          <p>Managers stay in control while the app helps surface what needs attention.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    
    <section class="section smart-kitchen-pitch">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Smart Kitchen includes the full intelligence layer</p>
          <h2>Smart Kitchen adds ordering, inventory, and menu intelligence to the daily workflow.</h2>
          <p>Shift and Operations help organize the day. Smart Kitchen adds the stronger intelligence layer: AI-assisted ordering, Menu Intelligence, invoice/menu scan intelligence, AI Forecast, price warnings, waste/par insights, recipe/menu costing signals, Manager Brief intelligence, and 86Voice menu-impact support.</p>
          <div class="audit-list">
            <span>Build smarter vendor-grouped order drafts.</span>
            <span>See what ingredients affect menu items before a stockout hurts service.</span>
            <span>Catch price jumps, waste patterns, and par issues earlier.</span>
            <span>Turn Manager Brief into an actual decision board, not just a morning note.</span>
          </div>
          <a class="button" href="pricing.html">Compare plans</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-suite-card panel reveal delay-1">
          <p class="eyebrow">Recommended plan</p>
          <h3>Smart Kitchen</h3>
          <p>The plan for restaurants that want the app to help protect food cost, reduce waste, improve ordering, and show managers what needs attention.</p>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Launch price</span><strong>$179/mo</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row good"><span>Founder year one</span><strong>$89.50/mo</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section ai-order-section">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">AI-assisted ordering</p>
          <h2>AI-assisted ordering that uses the whole restaurant picture.</h2>
          <p>86 Chaos can help build order drafts from stock, pars, pending orders, events, prep needs, menu links, burn/waste logs, and invoice history. That means ordering can become faster, smarter, and less dependent on memory.</p>
          <div class="audit-list">
            <span>Vendor-grouped AI order drafts.</span>
            <span>Event supply planning and prep prediction.</span>
            <span>Invoice price warnings and waste/par warning cards.</span>
            <span>Apply AI suggestions to the normal Order screen for review.</span>
          </div>
          <a class="button" href="ai-tools.html">Explore AI + Ordering</a>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-order-card panel reveal delay-1">
          <p class="eyebrow">Manager asks</p>
          <h3>“What should I order?”</h3>
          <div class="ai-order-result">
            <span>Checks stock + par</span>
            <span>Looks at event needs</span>
            <span>Flags waste and price warnings</span>
            <span>Builds a draft by vendor</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

<section class="section voice-home-section">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">86Voice</p>
          <h2>86Voice: built for busy hands and loud kitchens.</h2>
          <p>Instead of stopping the shift to hunt through screens, managers and staff can use natural kitchen language for prep, tasks, reminders, 86 alerts, maintenance, waste, status questions, and AI-assisted ordering.</p>
          <div class="audit-list">
            <span>“Prep two pans of onions.”</span>
            <span>“We’re out of chicken breast.”</span>
            <span>“What should I order?”</span>
            <span>“Add buns to the order draft.”</span>
          </div>
          <a class="button" href="86voice.html">Explore 86Voice</a>
        </div>
        <div class="voice-demo-card panel reveal delay-1">
          <div class="voice-pulse">86</div>
          <h3>“Add clean fryer wall to tasks.”</h3>
          <div class="voice-result">
            <span>Intent: Create task</span>
            <span>Category: Weekly cleaning</span>
            <span>Assigned: Kitchen team</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section feature-band">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">The operating layer</p>
          <h2>One place for the shift, the kitchen, and the numbers.</h2>
          <p>Start simple: prep lists, schedule, reminders, and 86 alerts. As the restaurant gets comfortable, layer in invoices, recipes, maintenance, daily close, and labor visibility.</p>
          <div class="bullet-cloud">
            <span>Prep Lists</span><span>86 Alerts</span><span>Inventory</span><span>Recipes</span><span>Daily Close</span><span>Labor</span><span>Maintenance</span><span>Reminders</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel mini-dashboard reveal delay-1">
          <h3>Today at a glance</h3>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Prep completion</span><strong>18 / 34</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Open 86 alerts</span><strong>3</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Invoices this month</span><strong>$5,393.76</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row"><span>Repairs open</span><strong>7</strong></div>
          <div class="mini-row good"><span>Cash variance</span><strong>$620</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section compact-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head center reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Common concerns</p>
          <h2>Built to fit around the restaurant you already run.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="compact-feature-list reveal">
          <div><strong>“I do not want another app.”</strong><span>86 Chaos is meant to replace scattered notes, texts, paper, spreadsheets, and memory with one kitchen-focused operating layer.</span></div>
          <div><strong>“My staff will not use it.”</strong><span>Simple daily workflows and 86Voice reduce the amount of tapping and training needed during a shift.</span></div>
          <div><strong>“We already have a POS.”</strong><span>Keep it. 86 Chaos works around the POS by handling prep, 86s, ordering support, schedules, maintenance, reminders, and manager visibility. Direct POS integrations are planned and being worked on.</span></div>
          <div><strong>“AI sounds risky.”</strong><span>AI suggests, drafts, alerts, explains, and analyzes. Managers approve actions that change business records or spend money.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-card">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Founder Beta</span>
          <h2>Try 86 Chaos free for 90 days.</h2>
          <p>90 days free, no credit card, no purchase required, and free setup during beta. Accepted restaurants help shape the product and receive 50% off the first location for the first paid year.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button" href="beta.html">Apply Free</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
